==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Sensory
<hw>Sen"so*ry</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>Of or
pertaining to the sensorium or sensation; <as>as, <ex>sensory</ex>
impulses; -- especially applied to those nerves and nerve fibers which
convey to a nerve center impulses resulting in sensation; also sometimes
loosely employed in the sense of <ex>afferent</ex>, to indicate nerve
fibers which convey impressions of any kind to a nerve
center</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sensual</ent>⟦br⟧
